obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25451)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `* Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25451&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prevention of Illicit`
  line `Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1988.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 4th day of July, 1988.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25452)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25452&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means, as respects a detention order made by the Central`
  line `Government or by an officer of the Central Government, or a person detained under such order, the`
  line `Central Government, and as respects a detention order made by a State Government or by an officer`
  line `of a State Government, or a person detained under such order, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "customs airport" means any airport appointed under clause (a) of section 7 of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) to be a customs airport;`
  line
  line `(c) "detention order" means an order made under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "foreigner" has the same meaning as in the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(e) "illicit traffic", in relation to narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, means--`
  line
  line `(i) cultivating any coca plant or gathering any portion of coca plant;`
  line
  line `(ii) cultivating the opium poppy or any cannabis plant;`
  line
  line `(iii) engaging in the production, manufacture, possession, sale, purchase, transportation,`
  line `warehousing, concealment, use or consumption, import inter-State, export inter-State, import into`
  line `India, export from India or transhipment, of narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances;`
  line
  line `(iv) dealing in any activities in narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances other than those`
  line `provided in sub-clauses (i) to (iii); or`
  line
  line `(v) handling or letting any premises for the carrying on of any of the activities referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (i) to (iv),`
  line
  line `other than those permitted under the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of`
  line `1985), or any rule or order made, or any condition of any licence, term or authorisation issued,`
  line `thereunder and includes--`
  line
  line `(1) financing, directly or indirectly, any of the aforementioned activities;`
  line
  line `(2) abetting or conspiring in the furtherance of or in support of doing any of the`
  line `aforementioned activities; and`
  line
  line `(3) harbouring persons engaged in any of the aforementioned activities;`
  line
  line `(f) "Indian customs waters" has the same meaning as in clause (28) of section 2 of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(g) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(h) words and expressions used herein but not defined, and defined in the Narcotic Drugs and`
  line `Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985), have the meanings respectively assigned to them in`
  line `that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25453)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to make orders detaining certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25453&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or a State`
  line `Government, or any officer of the Central Government, not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to that`
  line `Government, specially empowered for the purposes of this section by that Government, or any officer of a`
  line `State Government, not below the rank of a Secretary to that Government, specially empowered for the`
  line `purposes of this section by that Government, may, if satisfied, with respect to any person (including a`
  line `foreigner) that, with a view to preventing him from engaging in illicit traffic in narcotic drugs and`
  line `psychotropic substances, it is necessary so to do, make an order directing that such person be detained.`
  line
  line `(2) When any order of detention is made by a State Government or by an officer empowered by a`
  line `State Government, the State Government shall, within ten days, forward to the Central Government a`
  line `report in respect of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of clause (5) of article 22 of the Constitution, the communication to a person`
  line `detained in pursuance of a detention order of the grounds on which the order has been made shall be made`
  line `as soon as may be after the detention, but ordinarily not later than five days, and in exceptional`
  line `circumstances and for reasons to be recorded in writing not later than fifteen days, from the date of`
  line detention.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25454)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Execution of detention orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25454&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A detention order may be executed at any place in India in the`
  line `manner provided for the execution of warrants of arrest under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25455)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to regulate place and conditions of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25455&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every person in respect of whom a`
  line `detention order has been made shall be liable--`
  line
  line `(a) to be detained in such place and under such conditions including conditions as to`
  line `maintenance, interviews or communication with others, discipline and punishment for breaches of`
  line `discipline, as the appropriate Government may, by general or special order, specify; and`
  line
  line `(b) to be removed from one place of detention to another place of detention, whether within the`
  line `same State or in another State by order of the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made by a State Government under clause (b) for the removal of a`
  line `person from one State to another State except with the consent of the Government of that other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25456)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Grounds of detention severable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25456&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Where a person has been detained in pursuance of an order of`
  line `detention under sub-section (1) of section 3 which has been made on two or more grounds, such order of`
  line `detention shall be deemed to have been made separately on each of such grounds and accordingly`
  line
  line `(a) such order shall not be deemed to be invalid or inoperative merely because one or some of the`
  line `grounds is or are`
  line
  line `(i) vague,`
  line
  line `(ii) non-existent,`
  line
  line `(iii) not relevant,`
  line
  line `(iv) not connected or not proximately connected with such person, or`
  line
  line `(v) invalid for any other reason whatsoever,`
  line
  line `and it is not therefore possible to hold that the Government or officer making such order would have`
  line `been satisfied as provided in sub-section (1) of section 3 with reference to the remaining ground or`
  line `grounds and made the order of detention;`
  line
  line `(b) the Government or officer making the order of detention shall be deemed to have made the`
  line `order of detention under the said sub-section (1) after being satisfied as provided in that sub-section`
  line `with reference to the remaining ground or grounds.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25457)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Detention orders not to be invalid or inoperative on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25457&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No detention order`
  line `shall be invalid or inoperative merely by reason--`
  line
  line `(a) that the person to be detained thereunder is outside the limits of the territorial jurisdiction of`
  line `the Government or the officer making the order of detention; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the place of detention of such person is outside the said limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25458)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers in relation to absconding persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25458&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the appropriate Government has reason to`
  line `believe that a person in respect of whom a detention order has been made has absconded or is concealing`
  line `himself so that the order cannot be executed, that Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) make a report in writing of the fact to a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of the first`
  line `class having jurisdiction in the place where the said person ordinarily resides; and thereupon the`
  line `provisions of sections 82, 83, 84 and 85 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall`
  line `apply in respect of the said person and his property as if the order directing that he be detained were a`
  line `warrant issued by the Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) by order notified in the Official Gazette direct the said person to appear before such officer, at`
  line `such place and within such period as may be specified in the order; and if the said person fails to`
  line `comply with such direction, he shall, unless he proves that it was not possible for him to comply`
  line `therewith and that he had, within the period specified in the order, informed the officer mentioned in`
  line `the order of the reason which rendered compliance therewith impossible and of his whereabouts, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every`
  line `offence under clause (b) of sub- section (1) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25459)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Advisory Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25459&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sub-clause (a) of clause (4) and sub-clause (c) of clause`
  line `(7) of article 22 of the Constitution,`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government and each State Government shall, whenever necessary, constitute one`
  line `or more Advisory Boards each of which shall consist of a Chairman and two other persons possessing`
  line `the qualifications specified in sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of article 22 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) save as otherwise provided in section 10, the appropriate Government shall, within five weeks`
  line `from the date of detention of a person under a detention order, make a reference in respect thereof to`
  line `the Advisory Board constituted under clause (a) to enable the Advisory Board to make the report`
  line `under sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of article 22 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) the Advisory Board to which a reference is made under clause (b) shall after considering the`
  line `reference and the materials placed before it and after calling for such further information as it may`
  line `deem necessary from the appropriate Government or from any person called for the purpose through`
  line `the appropriate Government or from the person concerned, and if, in any particular case, it considers`
  line `it essential so to do or if the person concerned desires to be heard in person, after hearing him in`
  line `person, prepare its report specifying in a separate paragraph thereof its opinion as to whether or not`
  line `there is sufficient cause for the detention of the person concerned and submit the same within eleven`
  line `weeks from the date of detention of the person concerned;`
  line
  line `(d) when there is a difference of opinion among the members forming the Advisory Board, the`
  line `opinion of the majority of such members shall be deemed to be the opinion of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) a person against whom an order of detention has been made under this Act shall not be`
  line `entitled to appear by any legal practitioner in any matter connected with the reference to the Advisory`
  line `Board and the proceedings of the Advisory Board and its report, excepting that part of the report in`
  line `which the opinion of the Advisory Board is specified, shall be confidential;`
  line
  line `(f) in every case where the Advisory Board has reported that there is in its opinion sufficient`
  line `cause for the detention of a person, the appropriate Government may confirm the detention order and`
  line `continue the detention of the person concerned for such period as it thinks fit and in every case where`
  line `the Advisory Board has reported that there is in its opinion no sufficient cause for the detention of the`
  line `person concerned, the appropriate Government shall revoke the detention order and cause the person`
  line `to be released forthwith.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25460)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Cases in which and circumstances under which persons may be detained for periods longer than three months without obtaining the opinion of Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1996, s. 2, for "31st day of July, 1996" (w.e.f. 30-7-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25460&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, any person (including a foreigner) in respect of whom an order of detention is made`
  line `under this Act at any time before the ^1`
  line `[31st day of July, 1999] may be detained without obtaining, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of article 22 of the Constitution, the opinion`
  line `of an Advisory Board for a period longer than three months but not exceeding six months from the date of`
  line `his detention, where the order of detention has been made against such person with a view to preventing`
  line `him from engaging in illicit traffic in narcotic drugs and psychotropic substances, and the Central`
  line `Government or any officer of the Central Government, not below the rank of an Additional Secretary to`
  line `that Government, specially empowered for the purposes of this section by that Government, is satisfied`
  line `that such person engages or is likely to engage in illicit traffic in narcotic drugs and psychotropic`
  line `substances into, out of, through or within any area highly vulnerable to such illicit traffic and makes a`
  line `declaration to that effect within five weeks of the detention of such person.`
  line
  line `Explanation1.--In this sub-section, "area highly vulnerable to such illicit traffic" means--`
  line
  line `(i) the India customs waters;`
  line
  line `(ii) the customs airports;`
  line
  line `(iii) the metropolitan cities of Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi, Madras and the city of Varanasi;`
  line
  line `(iv) the inland area one hundred kilo metres in width from the coast of India falling within the`
  line `territories of the States of Andhra Pradesh, Goa, Gujarat, Karnataka, Kerala, Maharashtra, Orissa,`
  line `Tamil Nadu and West Bengal and the Union territories of Daman and Diu and Pondicherry;`
  line
  line `(v) the inland area one hundred kilo metres in width from--`
  line
  line `(a) the India-Pakistan border in the States of Gujarat, Punjab and Rajasthan;`
  line
  line `(b) the India-Nepal border in the States of Bihar, Sikkim, Uttar Pradesh and West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(c) the India-Burma border in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Manipur, Mizoram and`
  line Nagaland;
  line
  line `(d) the India-Bangladesh border in the States of Assam, Meghalaya, Tripura and West`
  line Bengal;
  line
  line `(e) the India-Bhutan border in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Sikkim and West`
  line Bengal;
  line
  line `(vi) such other area or customs station, as the Central Government may, having regard to the`
  line `vulnerability of such area or customs station, as the case may be, to illicit traffic, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of Explanation 1, "customs station" has the same meaning as in`
  line `clause (13) of section 2 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any person detained under a detention order to which the provisions of sub-section`
  line `(1) apply, section 9 shall have effect subject to the following modifications, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (b), for the words "shall, within five weeks", the words "shall, within four months`
  line `and two weeks" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (c),--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "the detention of the person concerned", the words "the continued detention`
  line `of the person concerned" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "eleven weeks", the words "five months and three weeks" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(iii) in clause (f), for the words "for the detention", at both the places where they occur, the words`
  line `"for the continued detention" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25461)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Maximum period of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25461&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The maximum period for which any person may be detained in`
  line `pursuance of any detention order to which the provisions of section 10 do not apply and which has been`
  line `confirmed under clause (f) of section 9 shall be one year from the date of detention, and the maximum`
  line `period for which any person may be detained in pursuance of any detention order to which the provisions`
  line `of section 10 apply and which has been confirmed under clause (f) of section 9, read with sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 10, shall be two years from the date of detention:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the power of appropriate Government in`
  line `either case to revoke or modify the detention order at any earlier time.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25462)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Revocation of detention orders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25462&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 21 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), a detention order may, at any time, be revoked or modified--`
  line
  line `(a) notwithstanding that the order has been made by an officer of a State Government, by that`
  line `State Government or by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that the order has been made by an officer of the Central Government or by a`
  line `State Government, by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The revocation of a detention order shall not bar the making of another detention order under`
  line `section 3 against the same person.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25463)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Temporary release of persons detaine`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25463&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, at any time, direct`
  line `that any person detained in pursuance of a detention order made by that Government or by an officer`
  line `subordinate to that Government or by a State Government or by an officer subordinate to a State`
  line `Government, may be released for any specified period either without conditions or upon such conditions`
  line `specified in the direction as that person accepts, and may, at any time, cancel his release.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Government may, at any time, direct that any person detained in pursuance of a detention`
  line `order made by that Government or by an officer subordinate to that Government may be released for any`
  line `specified period either without conditions or upon such conditions specified in the direction as the person`
  line `accepts, and may, at any time, cancel his release.`
  line
  line `(3) In directing the release of any person under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Government`
  line `directing the release may require him to enter into a bond with sureties for the due observance of the`
  line `conditions specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person released under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall surrender himself at the time`
  line `and place, and to the authority, specified in the order directing his release, or cancelling his release, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) If any person fails without sufficient cause to surrender himself in the manner specified in subsection`
  line `(4), he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person released under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) fails to fulfil any of the conditions`
  line `imposed upon him under the said sub-section or in the bond entered into by him, the bond shall be`
  line `declared to be forfeited and any person bound thereby shall be liable to pay the penalty thereof.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law and save as otherwise provided in this`
  line `section, no person against whom a detention order made under this Act is in force shall be released`
  line `whether on bail or bail bond or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25464)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905&sectionId=25464&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00002_198846_1517807317905
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government or a State Government and no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person for anything in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
